  "markdown_debrief": "### SHARP 4.0 Cognitive & Surgical Debrief\n\n> **💡 GAMED: Your immune system's elite five.**\n\n---\n\n## S — Set the Stage\nThe correct answer identifies IgA, IgD, and IgE as recognized classes of human immunoglobulins. These are fundamental components of the adaptive immune system, crucial for host defense against pathogens and central to understanding immune responses in clinical practice.\n\n## H — Highlight Excellence\nImmunoglobulins, or antibodies, are glycoproteins produced by plasma cells that play a critical role in humoral immunity. Each of the five major classes (IgG, IgA, IgM, IgD, IgE) has distinct structural features, tissue distribution, and effector functions. For instance, IgA is predominant in mucosal secretions, IgD is primarily found on naive B cell surfaces, and IgE is critically involved in allergic reactions and parasitic defense. Understanding these specific roles is vital for diagnosing and managing a wide range of immune-related conditions, from infections to autoimmune diseases and allergies.\n\n## A — Address the Gaps\n\nOption B (Incorrect): 'IgB' is not a recognized class of human immunoglobulin.\nOption C (Incorrect): 'IgC' is not a recognized class of human immunoglobulin.\n\n## R — Review Learning Points\n\n| Immunoglobulin Class | Primary Location/Function | Clinical Relevance |\n|---|---|---|\n| IgA | Mucosal surfaces (gut, respiratory, urogenital), secretions (tears, saliva, milk) | Mucosal immunity, secretory immunity, selective IgA deficiency |\n| IgD | Surface of naive B lymphocytes | B cell activation, antigen receptor |\n| IgE | Mast cells, basophils | Allergic reactions (Type I hypersensitivity), parasitic infections |\n| IgG | Blood, extracellular fluid, crosses placenta | Most abundant, secondary immune response, opsonization, complement activation, neonatal immunity |\n| IgM | Surface of naive B lymphocytes, blood (pentamer) | Primary immune response, complement activation, B cell receptor |\n\n## P — Plan (Board Pearl)\nBoard Pearl: Remember the five Ig classes: GAMED.\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Imaging & Intraoperative Pearl\nWhile immunoglobulins are not directly visualized, their effects can be. In severe IgE-mediated anaphylaxis during surgery, one might observe diffuse urticaria, angioedema, or bronchospasm on monitoring, requiring immediate intervention.\n\n## 📋 Guideline Anchor\nWorld Health Organization (WHO) Classification of Primary Immunodeficiencies (2022). Recommends diagnostic criteria and management strategies for conditions often involving immunoglobulin deficiencies or dysregulation.\n\n---\n\n### Answer Breakdown\n| Option | Text | Status |\n|--------|------|--------|\n| A | A | ✅ Correct |\n| B | B. | ❌ Incorrect |\n| C | C: | ❌ Incorrect |\n| D | D | ✅ Correct |\n| E | E. | ✅ Correct |\n\n**✅ Answer: A, D, E) ['A', 'D', 'E.']** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Difficulty: Easy** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Source: 1001 MCQs**\n",
